Class Lifeform

  • java.lang.Object
    • simpplle.comcode.Lifeform
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Externalizable, java.io.Serializable

    public class Lifeform
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Externalizable
    The University of Montana owns copyright of the designated documentation contained within this file as part of the software product designated by Uniform Resource Identifier UM-OpenSIMPPLLE-1.0. By copying this file the user accepts the University of Montana Open Source License Contract pertaining to this documentation and agrees to abide by all restrictions, requirements, and assertions contained therein.     This class contains methods for Lifeforms. Choices of lifeforms are TREES, SHRUBS, HERBACIOUS, AGRICULTURE, NA. Lifeforms will have individual species. Methods for these can be found in species.java

      • get

        public static Lifeform get(java.lang.String name)
        Gets the lifeform object from the string name. Objects returned will be trees, shrubs, herbacious, agriculture, no classification. The corresponding lifeforms strings are TREES, SHRUBS, HERBACIOUS, AGRICULTURE, NA
        Parameters:
        name - name of life forms (uppercase)
        Returns:
        lifeform object from allLifeforms hash map (lowercase)

      • get

        public static Lifeform get(int id)
        returns the lifeform in all values [] based on indexing lifeform ID. Choices are 0 - TREES, 1 - SHRUBS, 2 -HERBACIOUS, 3 -AGRICULTURE, 4 -NA
        Parameters:
        id - the lifeform id (0,1,2, or 3)
        Returns:
        lifeform object

      • findDominant

        public static Lifeform findDominant(java.util.Set<Lifeform> lives)
        Finds the dominant lifeform by first setting the dominant lifeform to the highest ID value but lowest dominance (3 = NA) then loops through the lifeforms id's to find the minimum ID. THis will be the dominant lifeform because lower ID's have higher dominance.
        Parameters:
        lives - the collection of lifeforms
        Returns:
        the dominant lifeform

      • getMoreDominant

        public static java.util.ArrayList<Lifeform> getMoreDominant(Lifeform lifeform)
        Method to make an arraylist of life forms that are more dominant (more dominant = lower Id.. The list will be in ascending order
        Parameters:
        lifeform -
        Returns:
        arraylist of increasingly more dominant species than passed life form

      • getLowerLifeform

        public static Lifeform getLowerLifeform(Lifeform lifeform)
        Finds a lower life form. Loops through all the lifeforms to find a lower dominance lifeform if there is any. Higher ID's correspond to lower dominance.
        Parameters:
        lifeform - the lifeform to be compared. Choices for lifeforms are TREES, SHRUBS, HERBACIOUS, AGRICULTURE, NA
        Returns:
        lifeform with higher ID meaning less dominant than parameter lifeform, if any

      • getMostDominant

        public static Lifeform getMostDominant(Lifeform life,
                       Lifeform life2)
        Gets the more dominant of two lifeforms. Higher dominance corresponds to lower lifeform ID's
        Parameters:
        life - first life form to be compared
        life2 - second life form to be compared
        Returns:
        the lifeform with lesser ID and therefore higher dominance
